adams.flow.control.Flow
	-annotation
	This flow uses a global actor to derive a value used in the\nMathExpression actor\'s expression. It uses a special notation\nto reference the global actor and obtain the output of the actor:\n  @{global:[global-actor-name]}\nThe global source \"val\" calculates a value based on the variable\n\"val\". This calculated value is then used in the MathExpression\nactor inside the Trigger.
	-actor
		adams.flow.standalone.CallableActors
			-actor
				adams.flow.source.SequenceSource
					-name
					val
					-actor
						adams.flow.source.Variable
							-var-name
							val
					-actor
						adams.flow.transformer.Convert
							-conversion
								adams.data.conversion.StringToDouble
					-actor
						adams.flow.transformer.MathExpression
							-expression
							X*1000
					-actor
						adams.flow.transformer.Convert
							-name
							Convert-1
							-conversion
								adams.data.conversion.DoubleToInt
	-actor
		adams.flow.source.ForLoop
	-actor
		adams.flow.transformer.SetVariable
			-var-name
			val
	-actor
		adams.flow.control.Trigger
			-tee
				adams.flow.source.ForLoop
					-lower
					10
					-upper
					12
			-tee
				adams.flow.transformer.MathExpression
					-expression
					X+@{global:val}
			-tee
				adams.flow.sink.Display
	-flow-execution-listener
		adams.flow.execution.NullListener

